  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://vocab.ceda.ac.uk/ontology/cci#">
    <dc:publisher xml:lang="en">STFC</dc:publisher>
    <dc:description>&lt;h4&gt;OWL Classes&lt;/h4&gt;There are currently 11 classes in the ontology, each of which represents an entry in the DRS as well a two object properties to link sensors and platforms.&lt;h5&gt;OWL Classes&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=classes.svg&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Concept Schemes&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;The named individuals of each class are also represented as concepts in SKOS concept schemes: &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/dataType&gt;data type&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/ecv&gt;ecv&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/freq&gt;frequency&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/org&gt;institutes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/platform&gt;platforms&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/platformGrp&gt;platform groups&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/platformProg&gt;platform programmes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/procLev&gt;processing levels&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/product&gt;products&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/project&gt;projects&lt;/a&gt;,, and &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/sensor&gt;sensors&lt;/a&gt;. The use of a concept scheme allows easy navigation up and down the tree as well as providing relationships to concepts from other DRS. As well as relationships between sensors and platforms, each ECV concept is related to one or more data type concepts.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;SKOS Navigation Down the Concept Scheme&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;img src=../../../scheme/cci/conceptSchemeDown.svg /&gt;&lt;h5&gt;SKOS Navigation Up the Concept Scheme&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;img src=../../../scheme/cci/conceptSchemeUp.svg /&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Collections&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;The named individuals of each class are also represented as members in SKOS collections: &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/dataType&gt;data type&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/ecv&gt;ecv&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/freq&gt;frequency&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/org&gt;institutes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/platform&gt;platforms&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/platformGrp&gt;platform groups&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../scheme/cci/platformProg&gt;platform programs&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/procLev&gt;processing levels&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/product&gt;products&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/project&gt;projects&lt;/a&gt;,  and &lt;a href=../../../collection/cci/sensor&gt;sensors&lt;/a&gt;. As well as relationships between sensors and platforms, each ECV concept is related to one or more data type concepts.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;SKOS Collections&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;img src=../../../collection/cci/collection.svg /&gt;</dc:description>
    <dc:title>The CCI Ontology</dc:title>
    <dc:creator>Science and Technology Facilities Council</dc:creator>
    <rdfs:comment>This ontology represents the Directory Reference Scheme (DRS) used by the ESA Climate Change Initiative &lt;a href=http://cci.esa.int/&gt;CCI project&lt;/a&gt;.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#ConceptScheme"/>
    <dc:rights xml:lang="en">This work is licensed under a BSD license.</dc:rights>
    <rdfs:label>CCI Ontology</rdfs:label>
    <owl:versionInfo>0.0.1</owl:versionInfo>
    <dc:date>2026-03-18</dc:date>
